      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HOW AWESOME (7) is a last start placegetter in Grade 5 company, jumping from this box and finishing a 2 length second over 390m at this track. Has a very honest record from this same draw, including a win and four minors. Tough to beat on best. PAW PASCAL (2) was sent out long odds last time but rocketed out of the boxes with a fast early sectional and gave a sight before being swallowed up late, finishing a one length third (24.78) over 435m at Sale. Overdue and expected to feature again. BELAIR BLUE (1) has a fair record and proved too strong last time to win by a neck at Horsham in a handy 23.63 beating Zipping Tyra. Comes through a solid form race last start. Leading player again. PAW BASTOW (5) must be respected despite an unplaced effort here most recently.",
